ations.\\n\\n### Step 2: Cache `GetHooksDir()` result\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go`\\n\\nAdd a CWD-keyed cache (same pattern as `paths.RepoRoot()`). Add `ClearHooksDirCache()` for tests. The hooks dir doesn't change during a single CLI invocation.\\n\\n### Step 3: Make `OpenRepository()` use `paths.RepoRoot()`\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:560`\\n\\nReplace `GetWorktreePath()` with `paths.RepoRoot()` — same `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` but cached. By the time `OpenRepository()` runs in the enable flow, `paths.RepoRoot()` cache is already warm from `setup.go:71`.\\n\\n### Step 4: Pass `localDev` to `InstallGitHook()` and `CheckAndWarnHookManagers()`\\n\\n**Files:** `strategy/hooks.go`, `strategy/hook_managers.go`, `setup.go`, `manual_commit.go`, `auto_commit.go`\\n\\nCurrently `InstallGitHook()` calls `hookCmdPrefix()` → `isLocalDev()` → `settings.Load()` which re-reads 2 JSON files. The caller already knows `localDev`. Add a `localDev` parameter to eliminate the redundant reads.\\n\\nSame for `CheckAndWarnHookManagers()` which also calls `hookCmdPrefix()`.\\n\\nUpdate all callers (5-6 call sites in setup.go, manual_commit.go, auto_commit.go).\\n\\n### Step 5: Eliminate redundant work in `EnsureSetup()`\\n\\n**Files:** `strategy/manual_commit.go`, `strategy/auto_commit.go`, `setup.go`\\n\\nAdd `EnsureSetupWithOpts(opts)` alongside the existing parameterless `EnsureSetup()` (preserves backward compat, no interface change):\\n\\n```go\\ntype EnsureSetupOpts struct {\\n    SkipGitignore bool            // Already called EnsureEntireGitignore\\n    SkipHookCheck bool            // Already installed hooks\\n    Repo          *git.Repository // Reuse already-opened repo\\n    LocalDev      bool            // For InstallGitHook fallback\\n}\\n```\\n\\nIn `setup.go`, the enable paths pass:\\n- `SkipGitignore: true` (setupEntireDirectory already called it)\\n- `SkipHookCheck: true` (InstallGitHook already ran)\\n- `Repo: repo` (from the empty-repo check, when available)\\n\\n### Step 6: Add E2E wall-clock timing script (`mise run bench:enable`)\\n\\n**File:** `mise.toml` — new task `bench:enable`\\n\\nA shell script that measures real wall-clock time of the full compiled `entire enable --agent claude-code` binary in a fresh git repo. This captures the true end-to-end startup time including process launch, Go runtime init, and all I/O — not just the Go function internals.\\n\\nThe script:\\n1. Builds the `entire` binary once via `mise run build`\\n2. Creates a temp git repo with an initial commit\\n3. Runs `entire enable --agent claude-code --telemetry=false` N times (default 10), capturing wall-clock time via Go's `time` or the built-in `time` command\\n4. Reports min/median/max/mean times\\n5. Cleans up\\n\\nThis is non-deterministic but gives a clear before/after signal. Run it on main first, note the numbers, then run on the feature branch.\\n\\n```toml\\n[tasks.\\\"bench:enable\\\"]\\ndescription = \\\"Measure wall-clock time of 'entire enable' in a fresh repo\\\"\\nrun = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\\nset -euo pipefail\\n\\nRUNS=\\\"${BENCH_RUNS:-10}\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"=== Building entire binary ===\\\"\\nmise run build\\n\\nENTIRE=\\\"$(pwd)/entire\\\"\\nif [ ! -x \\\"$ENTIRE\\\" ]; then\\n  echo \\\"Build failed — binary not found\\\"\\n  exit 1\\nfi\\n\\ntmpdir=$(mktemp -d)\\ntrap 'rm -rf \\\"$tmpdir\\\"' EXIT\\n\\ntimes=()\\nfor i in $(seq 1 \\\"$RUNS\\\"); do\\n  # Fresh repo each run\\n  dir=\\\"$tmpdir/repo-$i\\\"\\n  mkdir -p \\\"$dir\\\"\\n  git -C \\\"$dir\\\" init -q\\n  git -C \\\"$dir\\\" commit --allow-empty -m \\\"init\\\" -q\\n\\n  # Measure wall-clock time (milliseconds)\\n  start=$(python3 -c 'import time; print(int(time.time()*1000))')\\n  (cd \\\"$dir\\\" && \\\"$ENTIRE\\\" enable --agent claude-code --telemetry=false) >/dev/null 2>&1\\n  end=$(python3 -c 'import time; print(int(time.time()*1000))')\\n  elapsed=$((end - start))\\n  times+=(\\\"$elapsed\\\")\\n  printf \\\"  Run %2d: %d ms\\\\n\\\" \\\"$i\\\" \\\"$elapsed\\\"\\ndone\\n\\n# Stats via python\\nprintf \\\"\\\\n=== Results (%d runs) ===\\\\n\\\" \\\"$RUNS\\\"\\npython3 -c \\\"\\nimport statistics\\nt = [$(IFS=,; echo \\\"${times[*]}\\\")]\\nprint(f'  Min:    {min(t)} ms')\\nprint(f'  Median: {int(statistics.median(t))} ms')\\nprint(f'  Mean:   {int(statistics.mean(t))} ms')\\nprint(f'  Max:    {max(t)} ms')\\nprint(f'  Stdev:  {int(statistics.stdev(t))} ms')\\n\\\"\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n```\\n\\nUsage: Run on main first to get a baseline, then on the feature branch to compare.\\n\\n```bash\\n# On main\\ngit stash && git checkout main\\nmise run bench:enable    # note the median\\ngit checkout - && git stash pop\\n\\n# On feature branch (after optimizations)\\nmise run bench:enable    # compare median\\n```\\n\\n### Step 7: Verify against main\\n\\n```bash\\n# Go benchmarks (deterministic, statistical comparison)\\nBENCH_PATTERN=BenchmarkEnableCommand mise run bench:compare\\n\\n# E2E wall-clock (real binary, non-deterministic but shows real-world impact)\\nmise run bench:enable\\n```\\n\\n## Files Changed\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|---|---|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/bench_enable_test.go` | **New** — enable benchmarks |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go` | Cache `GetHooksDir()`, add `localDev` param to `InstallGitHook()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hook_managers.go` | Add `localDev` param to `CheckAndWarnHookManagers()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go` | `OpenRepository()` uses `paths.RepoRoot()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go` | Add `EnsureSetupWithOpts()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go` | Add `EnsureSetupWithOpts()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/setup.go` | Pass opts through to eliminate redundant work |\\n| `mise.toml` | New `bench:enable` task for E2E wall-clock timing |\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci` — all tests pass\\n2. `mise run bench` — Go benchmarks run\\n3. `BENCH_PATTERN=Bench