":\"Here is a thorough summary of each file's relevant sections:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go`\\n\\n### `GetHooksDir()` (line 46-48)\\n```go\\nfunc GetHooksDir() (string, error) {\\n\\treturn getHooksDirInPath(\\\".\\\")\\n}\\n```\\nDelegates to `getHooksDirInPath(\\\".\\\")` which runs `git rev-parse --git-path hooks` (a child process spawn for every call). Returns the active hooks directory respecting `core.hooksPath` and linked worktrees.\\n\\n### `getHooksDirInPath(dir string)` (line 76-91)\\n```go\\nfunc getHooksDirInPath(dir string) (string, error) {\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"git\\\", \\\"rev-parse\\\", \\\"--git-path\\\", \\\"hooks\\\")\\n\\tcmd.Dir = dir\\n\\toutput, err := cmd.Output()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\", errors.New(\\\"not a git repository\\\")\\n\\t}\\n\\thooksDir := strings.TrimSpace(string(output))\\n\\tif !filepath.IsAbs(hooksDir) {\\n\\t\\thooksDir = filepath.Join(dir, hooksDir)\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn filepath.Clean(hooksDir), nil\\n}\\n```\\n**Key note**: Spawns a `git` child process every invocation. No caching.\\n\\n### `InstallGitHook(silent bool) (int, error)` (line 169-222)\\n```go\\nfunc InstallGitHook(silent bool) (int, error) {\\n\\thooksDir, err := GetHooksDir()\\n\\t// ... MkdirAll(hooksDir, 0o755)\\n\\tspecs := buildHookSpecs(hookCmdPrefix())\\n\\tinstalledCount := 0\\n\\tfor _, spec := range specs {\\n\\t\\t// For each of 4 hooks: read existing, check marker, backup if needed, write if changed\\n\\t\\thookPath := filepath.Join(hooksDir, spec.name)\\n\\t\\t// ... backup logic, chain logic, writeHookFile()\\n\\t}\\n\\tif !silent { /* print */ }\\n\\treturn installedCount, nil\\n}\\n```\\nCalls `GetHooksDir()` (1 subprocess), then `hookCmdPrefix()` which calls `isLocalDev()` which calls `settings.Load()`. Then iterates 4 hooks, reading/writing each.\\n\\n### `hookCmdPrefix()` (line 301-306)\\n```go\\nfunc hookCmdPrefix() string {\\n\\tif isLocalDev() {\\n\\t\\treturn \\\"go run ./cmd/entire/main.go\\\"\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn \\\"entire\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### `isLocalDev()` (line 310-316)\\n```go\\nfunc isLocalDev() bool {\\n\\ts, err := settings.Load()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn false\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn s.LocalDev\\n}\\n```\\nCalls `settings.Load()` which reads settings files from disk. No caching at this level -- the settings package may have its own caching.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hook_managers.go`\\n\\n### `CheckAndWarnHookManagers(w io.Writer)` (line 114-130)\\n```go\\nfunc CheckAndWarnHookManagers(w io.Writer) {\\n\\trepoRoot, err := paths.RepoRoot()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\tmanagers := detectHookManagers(repoRoot)\\n\\tif len(managers) == 0 {\\n\\t\\treturn\\n\\t}\\n\\twarning := hookManagerWarning(managers, hookCmdPrefix())\\n\\tif warning != \\\"\\\" {\\n\\t\\tfmt.Fprintln(w)\\n\\t\\tfmt.Fprint(w, warning)\\n\\t}\\n}\\n```\\nCalls `paths.RepoRoot()` (cached by CWD), then `detectHookManagers()` which does filesystem-only checks (up to ~20 `os.Stat` calls for lefthook variants + 3 other checks). Then calls `hookCmdPrefix()` which again calls `isLocalDev()` -> `settings.Load()`.\\n\\n### `detectHookManagers(repoRoot string) []hookManager` (line 22-54)\\nBuilds a list of up to ~19 `hookManager` checks (Husky, pre-commit, Overcommit, plus 16 Lefthook variants), does `os.Stat()` on each. Returns matches (deduped by name).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go`\\n\\n### `OpenRepository() (*git.Repository, error)` (line 560-577)\\n```go\\nfunc OpenRepository() (*git.Repository, error) {\\n\\trepoRoot, err := GetWorktreePath()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\trepoRoot = \\\".\\\"\\n\\t}\\n\\trepo, err := git.PlainOpenWithOptions(repoRoot, &git.PlainOpenOptions{\\n\\t\\tEnableDotGitCommonDir: true,\\n\\t})\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to open repository: %w\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn repo, nil\\n}\\n```\\n**Key note**: Calls `GetWorktreePath()` which spawns `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` every time. Then opens the repo with go-git. **No caching** -- every caller gets a new `git.Repository`. This is called extremely frequently throughout the codebase.\\n\\n### `GetWorktreePath() (string, error)` (line 661-669)\\n```go\\nfunc GetWorktreePath() (string, error) {\\n\\tctx := context.Background()\\n\\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, \\\"git\\\", \\\"rev-parse\\\", \\\"--show-toplevel\\\")\\n\\toutput, err := cmd.Output()\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn \\\"\\\", fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to get worktree path: %w\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn strings.TrimSpace(string(output)), nil\\n}\\n```\\n**No caching**. Spawns a git subprocess every call. Compare with `paths.RepoRoot()` which does the same thing but with caching.\\n\\n### `EnsureEntireGitignore()` (line 673-723)\\nReads `.entire/.gitignore`, checks for 4 required entries (`tmp/`, `settings.local.json`, `metadata/`, `logs/`), appends missing ones. Calls `paths.AbsPath()` which calls `paths.RepoRoot()` (cached).\\n\\n### `EnsureMetadataBranch(repo *git.Repository) error` (line 261-316)\\nChecks if `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch exists. If not, creates an orphan commit with empty tree and creates the branch reference. Prints to stderr on creation.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/setup.go`\\n\\n### `EnsureSetup()` is not a standalone function -- it's called on strategy objects. The setup flow is in these key functions:\\n\\n### `setupAgentHooksNonInteractive(w io.Writer, ag agent.Agent, strategyName string, localDev, forceHooks, skipPushSessions, telemetry bool) error` (line 707-806)\\nThe non-interactive `entire enable --agent` path. Order of operations:\\n1. `hookAgent.InstallHooks(localDev, forceHooks)` -- install agent-specific hooks\\n2. `setupEntireDirectory()` -- create `.entire/` and gitignore\\n3. `LoadEntireSettings()` -- load existing settings\\n4. Update settings fields (enabled, strategy, localDev, push_sessions, telemetry)\\n5. `SaveEntireSettings(settings)` -- write settings\\n6. `strategy.InstallGitHook(true)` -- install 4 git hooks (spawns `git rev-parse --git-path hooks`)\\n7. `strategy.CheckAndWarnHookManagers(w)` -- detect hook managers (more filesystem checks)\\n8. `strategy.Get(settings.Strategy)` -- get strategy instance\\n9. `strat.EnsureSetup()` -- strategy-specific setup (creates metadata branch, etc.)\\n\\n### `setupEntireDirectory() (bool, error)` (line 844-869)\\n```go\\nfunc setupEntireDirectory() (bool, error) {\\n\\tentireDirAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(paths.EntireDir)\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\tentireDirAbs = paths.EntireDir\\n\\t}\\n\\tcreated := false\\n\\tif _, err := os.Stat(entireDirAbs); os.IsNotExist(err) {\\n\\t\\tcreated = true\\n\\t}\\n\\tif err := os.MkdirAll(entireDirAbs, 0o755); err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn false, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to create .entire directory: %w\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\tif err := strategy.EnsureEntireGitignore(); err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn false, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to setup .gitignore: %w\\\", err)\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn created, nil\\n}\\n```\\nCalls `paths.AbsPath()` (which calls `RepoRoot()`), then `os.MkdirAll()`, then `strategy.EnsureEntireGitignore()` (which also calls `paths.AbsPath()`).\\n\\n### `runEnableWithStrategy(...)` (line 188-284) and `runEnableInteractive(...)` (line 288-389)\\nBoth follow the same pattern:\\n1. Uninstall deselected agent hooks\\n2. Setup agent hooks for each selected agent\\n3. `setupEntireDirectory()`\\n4. Load/save settings\\n5. `strategy.InstallGitHook(true)`\\n6. `strategy.CheckAndWarnHookManagers(w)`\\n7. `strat.EnsureSetup()`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. `/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit.go`\\n\\n### `ManualCommitStrategy.EnsureSetup() error` (line 99-120)\\n```go\\nfunc (s *Manual