s a checkpoint commit for a completed task.\",\"numLines\":50,\"startLine\":450,\"totalLines\":1106}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"b0788f2a-dacc-4756-a38a-2f6fa12c63e1\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"d4fe2e8f-1cd4-45eb-aee7-8d145b741afe\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"239c414d-2b2a-42d8-b557-85f3197d1015\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"enable_performance_optimzations\",\"slug\":\"woolly-toasting-corbato\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01GXtPG76RurTN8eWGRjCw8S\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01Y4AFii6cL3L1dTVC9oe8nW\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/strategy.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":45547,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":35635,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":45547},\"output_tokens\":4,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYLpXEhUbT5aY575vgeW3\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"905862c1-2420-4523-85de-9e2352304b5c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-21T07:28:45.673Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"905862c1-2420-4523-85de-9e2352304b5c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"239c414d-2b2a-42d8-b557-85f3197d1015\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"enable_performance_optimzations\",\"slug\":\"woolly-toasting-corbato\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Y4AFii6cL3L1dTVC9oe8nW\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01Y4AFii6cL3L1dTVC9oe8nW\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-21T07:28:45.681Z\",\"uuid\":\"446161a1-886c-491d-9a1e-94a53a8ca873\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"905862c1-2420-4523-85de-9e2352304b5c\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"239c414d-2b2a-42d8-b557-85f3197d1015\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"enable_performance_optimzations\",\"slug\":\"woolly-toasting-corbato\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Y4AFii6cL3L1dTVC9oe8nW\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→// Package strategy provides an interface for different git strategies\\n     2→// that can be used to save and manage Claude Code session changes.\\n     3→package strategy\\n     4→\\n     5→import (\\n     6→\\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    10→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    11→\\n    12→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n    13→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id\\\"\\n    14→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session\\\"\\n    15→)\\n    16→\\n    17→// ErrNoMetadata is returned when a commit does not have an Entire metadata trailer.\\n    18→var ErrNoMetadata = errors.New(\\\"commit has no entire metadata\\\")\\n    19→\\n    20→// ErrNoSession is returned when no session info is available.\\n    21→var ErrNoSession = errors.New(\\\"no session info available\\\")\\n    22→\\n    23→// ErrNotTaskCheckpoint is returned when a rewind point is not a task checkpoint.\\n    24→var ErrNotTaskCheckpoint = errors.New(\\\"not a task checkpoint\\\")\\n    25→\\n    26→// ErrEmptyRepository is returned when the repository has no commits yet.\\n    27→var ErrEmptyRepository = errors.New(\\\"repository has no commits yet\\\")\\n    28→\\n    29→// SessionIDConflictError is returned when trying to start a new session\\n    30→// but the shadow branch already has commits from a different session ID.\\n    31→// This prevents orphaning existing session work.\\n    32→type SessionIDConflictError struct {\\n    33→\\tExistingSession string // Session ID found in the shadow branch\\n    34→\\tNewSession      string // Session ID being initialized\\n    35→\\tShadowBranch    string // The shadow branch name (e.g., \\\"entire/abc1234\\\")\\n    36→}\\n    37→\\n    38→func (e *SessionIDConflictError) Error() string {\\n    39→\\treturn \\\"session ID conflict: shadow branch has commits from a different session\\\"\\n    40→}\\n    41→\\n    42→// ExtractToolUseIDFromTaskMetadataDir extracts the ToolUseID from a task metadata directory path.\\n    43→// Task metadata dirs have format: .entire/metadata/<session>/tasks/<toolUseID>\\n    44→// Returns empty string if not a task metadata directory.\\n    45→func ExtractToolUseIDFromTaskMetadataDir(metadataDir string) string {\\n    46→\\tparts := strings.Split(metadataDir, \\\"/\\\")\\n    47→\\tif len(parts) >= 2 && parts[len(parts)-2] == \\\"tasks\\\" {\\n    48→\\t\\treturn parts[len(parts)-1]\\n    49→\\t}\\n    50→\\treturn \\\"\\\"\\n    51→}\\n    52→\\n    53→// SessionInfo contains information about the current session state.\\n    54→// This is used to generate trailers for linking commits to their AI session.\\n    55→type SessionInfo struct {\\n    56→\\t// SessionID is the session identifier extracted from the latest commit's metadata\\n    57→\\tSessionID string\\n    58→\\n    59→\\t// Reference is a strategy-specific reference string.\\n    60→\\t// For manual-commit strategy: \\\"entire/abc1234\\\" (the shadow branch name)\\n    61→\\t// Empty for commit strategy (metadata is in the same commit).\\n    62→\\tReference string\\n    63→\\n    64→\\t// CommitHash is the full SHA of the commit containing the session metadata.\\n    65→\\t// Empty for commit strategy.\\n    66→\\tCommitHash string\\n    67→}\\n    68→\\n    69→// RewindPoint represents a point to which the user can rewind.\\n    70→// This abstraction allows different strategies to use different\\n    71→// identifiers (commit hashes, branch names, stash refs, etc.)\\n    72→type RewindPoint struct {\\n    73→\\t// ID is the unique identifier for this rewind point\\n    74→\\t// (commit hash, branch name, stash ref, etc.)\\n    75→\\tID string\\n    76→\\n    77→\\t// Message is the human-readable description/summary\\n    78→\\tMessage string\\n    79→\\n    80→\\t// MetadataDir is the path to the metadata directory\\n    81→\\tMetadataDir string\\n    82→\\n    83→\\t// Date is when this rewind point was created\\n    84→\\tDate time.Time\\n    85→\\n    86→\\t// IsTaskCheckpoint indicates if this is a task checkpoint (vs a session checkpoint)\\n    87→\\tIsTaskCheckpoint bool\\n    88→\\n    89→\\t// ToolUseID is the tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session checkpoints)\\n    90→\\tToolUseID string\\n    91→\\n    92→\\t// IsLogsOnly indicates this is a commit with session logs but no shadow branch state.\\n    93→\\t// The logs can be restored from entire/checkpoints/v1, but file state requires git checkout.\\n    94→\\tIsLogsOnly bool\\n    95→\\n    96→\\t// CheckpointID is the stable 12-hex-char identifier for logs-only points.\\n    97→\\t// Used to retrieve logs from entire/checkpoints/v1/<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/full.jsonl\\n    98→\\t// Empty for shadow branch checkpoints (uncommitted).\\n    99→\\tCheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n   100→\\n   101→\\t// Agent is the human-readable name of the agent that created this checkpoint\\n   102→\\t// (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\")\\n   103→\\tAgent agent.AgentType\\n   104→\\n   105→\\t// SessionID is the session identifier for this checkpoint.\\n   106→\\t// Used to distinguish checkpoints from different concurrent sessions.\\n   107→\\tSessionID string\\n   108→\\n   109→\\t// SessionPrompt is the initial prompt that started this session.\\n   110→\\t// Used to help users identify which session a checkpoint belongs to.\\n   111→\\tSessionPrompt string\\n   112→\\n   113→\\t// SessionCount is the number of sessions in this checkpoint (1 for single-session).\\n   114→\\t// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.\\n   115→\\tSessionCount int\\n   116→\\n   117→\\t// SessionIDs contains all session IDs when this is a multi-session checkpoint.\\n   118→\\t// The last entry is the most recent session (same as SessionID).\\n   119→\\t// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.\\n   120→\\tSessionIDs []string\\n   121→\\n   122→\\t// SessionPrompts contains the first prompt for each session (parallel to SessionIDs).\\n   123→\\t// Used to display context when showing resume commands for multi-session checkpoints.\\n   124→\\tSessionPrompts []string\\n   125→}\\n   126→\\n   127→// RewindPreview describes what will happen when rewinding to a checkpoint.\\n   128→// Used to warn users about files that will be modified or deleted.\\n   129→type RewindPreview struct {\\n   130→\\t// FilesToRestore are files from the checkpoint that will be written/restored.\\n   131→\\tFilesToRestore []string\\n   132→\\n   133→\\t// FilesToDelete are untracked files that will be removed.\\n   134→\\t// These are files created after the checkpoint that aren't in the checkpoint tree\\n   135→\\t// and weren't present at session start.\\n   136→\\tFilesToDelete []string\\n   137→\\n   138→\\t// TrackedChanges are tracked files with uncommitted changes that will be reverted.\\n   139→\\t// These come from the existing CanRewind() warning.\\n   140→\\tTrackedChanges []string\\n   141→}\\n   142→\\n   143→// StepContext contains all information needed for saving a step checkpoint.\\n   144→// All file paths should be pre-filtered and normalized by the CLI layer.\\n   145→type StepContext struct {\\n   146→\\t// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier\\n   147→\\tSessionID string\\n   148→\\n   149→\\t// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified during the session\\n   150→\\t// (extracted from the transcript, already filtered and relative)\\n   151→\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n   152→\\n   153→\\t// NewFiles is the list of new files created during the session\\n   154→\\t// (pre-computed by CLI from pre-prompt state comparison)\\n   155→\\tNewFiles []string\\n   156→\\n   157→\\t// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted during the session\\n   158→\\t// (tracked files that no longer exist)\\n   159→\\tDeletedFiles []string\\n   160→\\n   161→\\t// MetadataDir is the path to the session metadata directory\\n   162→\\tMetadataDir string\\n   163→\\n   164→\\t// MetadataDirAbs is the absolute path to the session metadata directory\\n   165→\\tMetadataDirAbs string\\n   166→\\n   167→\\t// CommitMessage is the generated commit message\\n   168→\\tCommitMessage string\\n   169→\\n   170→\\t// TranscriptPath is the path to the transcript file\\n   171→\\tTranscriptPath string\\n   172→\\n   173→\\t// AuthorName is the name to use for commits\\n   174→\\tAuthorName string\\n   175→\\n   176→\\t// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits\\n   177→\\tAuthorEmail string\\n   178→\\n   179→\\t// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\")\\n   180→\\tAgentType agent.AgentType\\n   181→\\n   182→\\t// Transcript position at step/turn start - tracks what was added during this step\\n   183→\\tStepTranscriptIdentifier string // Last identifier when step started (UUID for Claude, message ID for Gemini)\\n   184→\\tStepTranscriptStart      int    // Transcript line count when this step/turn started\\n   185→\\n   186→\\t// TokenUsage contains the token usage for this checkpoint\\n   187→\\tTokenUsage *agent.TokenUsage\\n   188→}\\n   189→\\n   190→// TaskStepContext contains all information needed for saving a task step checkpoint.\\n   191→// This is called by the PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.\\n   192→// The strategy is responsible for creating metadata structures and storing them\\n   193→// according to its storage approach.\\n   194→type TaskStepContext struct {\\n   195→\\t// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier\\n   196→\\tSessionID string\\n   197→\\n   198→\\t// ToolUseID is the unique identifier for this Task tool invocation\\n   199→\\tToolUseID string\\n   200→\\n   201→\\t// AgentID is the subagent identifier (from tool_response.agentId)\\n   202→\\tAgentID string\\n   203→\\n   204→\\t// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified by the subagent\\n   205→\\t// (extracted from the subagent's transcript)\\n   206→\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n   207→\\n   208→\\t// NewFiles is the list of new files created by the subagent\\n   209→\\t// (computed from pre-task state comparison)\\n   210→\\tNewFiles []string\\n   211→\\n   212→\\t// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted by the subagent\\n   213→\\tDeletedFiles []string\\n   214→\\n   215→\\t// TranscriptPath is the path to the main session transcript\\n   216→\\tTranscriptPath string\\n   217→\\n   218→\\t// SubagentTranscriptPath is the path to the subagent's transcript (if available)\\n   219→\\tSubagentTranscriptPath string\\n   220→\\n   221→\\t// CheckpointUUID is the UUID for transcript truncation when rewinding\\n   222→\\tCheckpointUUID string\\n   223→\\n   224→\\t// AuthorName is the name to use for commits\\n   225→\\tAuthorName string\\n   226→\\n   227→\\t// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits\\n   228→\\tAuthorEmail string\\n   229→\\n   230→\\t// IsIncremental indicates this is an incremental checkpoint during task execution,\\n   231→\\t// not a final task completion checkpoint. When true:\\n   232→\\t// - Writes to checkpoints/NNN-{tool-use-id}.json instead of checkpoint.json\\n   233→\\t// - Skips transcript handling\\n   234→\\t// - Uses incremental commit message\\n   235→\\tIsIncremental bool\\n   236→\\n   237→\\t// IncrementalSequence is the checkpoint sequence number (1, 2, 3, ...)\\n   238→\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n   239→\\tIncrementalSequence int\\n   240→\\n   241→\\t// IncrementalType is the tool that triggered this checkpoint (\\\"TodoWrite\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", etc.)\\n   242→\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n   243→\\tIncrementalType string\\n   244→\\n   245→\\t// IncrementalData is the tool_input payload for this checkpoint\\n   246→\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n   247→\\tIncrementalData json.RawMessage\\n   248→\\n   249→\\t// SubagentType is the type of subagent (e.g., \\\"dev\\\", \\\"reviewer\\\")\\n   250→\\t// Extracted from tool_input.subagent_type in Task tool\\n   251→\\t// Used for descriptive commit messages\\n   252→\\tSubagentType string\\n   253→\\n   254→\\t// TaskDescription is the task description provided to the subagent\\n   255→\\t// Extracted from tool_input.description in Task tool\\n   256→\\t// Used for descriptive commit messages\\n   257→\\tTaskDescription string\\n   258→\\n   259→\\t// TodoContent is the content of the in-progress todo item\\n   260→\\t// Extracted from tool_input.todos where status == \\\"in_progress\\\"\\n   261→\\t// Used for descriptive incremental checkpoint messages\\n   262→\\tTodoContent string\\n   263→\\n   264→\\t// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\")\\n   265→\\tAgentType agent.AgentType\\n   266→}\\n   267→\\n   268→// TaskCheckpoint contains the checkpoint information written to checkpoint.json\\n   269→type TaskCheckpoint struct {\\n   270→\\tSessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n   271→\\tToolUseID      string `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"`\\n   272→\\tCheckpointUUID string `json:\\\"checkpoint_uuid\\\"`\\n   273→\\tAgentID        string `json:\\\"agent_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n   274→}\\n   275→\\n   276→// SubagentCheckpoint represents an intermediate checkpoint created during subagent execution.\\n   277→// These are created by PostToolUse hooks for tools like TodoWrite, Edit, Write.\\n   278→type SubagentCheckpoint struct {\\n   279→\\tType      string          `json:\\\"type\\\"`        // Tool name: \\\"TodoWrite\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", \\\"Write\\\"\\n   280→\\tToolUseID string          `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"` // The tool use ID that created this checkpoint\\n   281→\\tTimestamp time.Time       `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`   // When the checkpoint was created\\n   282→\\tData      json.RawMessage `json:\\\"data\\\"`        // Type-specific payload (tool_input)\\n   283→}\\n   284→\\n   285→// TaskMetadataDir returns the path to a task's metadata directory\\n   286→// within the session metadata directory.\\n   287→func TaskMetadataDir(sessionMetadataDir, toolUseID string) string {\\n   288→\\treturn sessionMetadataDir + \\\"/tasks/\\\" + toolUseID\\n   289→}\\n   290→\\n   291→// ReadTaskCheckpoint reads the checkpoint.json file from a task metadata directory.\\n   292→// This is used during rewind to get the checkpoint UUID for transcript truncation.\\n   293→func ReadTaskCheckpoint(taskMetadataDir string) (*TaskCheckpoint, error) {\\n   294→\\tcheckpointFile := taskMetadataDir + \\\"/checkpoint.json\\\"\\n   295→\\n   296→\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(checkpointFile) //nolint:gosec // Reading from controlled git metadata path\\n   297→\\tif err != nil {\\n   298→\\t\\treturn nil, err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase\\n   299→\\t}\\n   300→\\n   301→\\tvar checkpoint TaskCheckpoint\\n   302→\\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &checkpoint); err != nil {\\n   303→\\t\\treturn nil, err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase\\n   304→\\t}\\n   305→\\n   306→\\treturn &checkpoint, nil\\n   307→}\\n   308→\\n   309→// Strategy defines the interface for git operation strategies.\\n   310→// Different implementations can use commits, branches, stashes, etc.\\n   311→//\\n   312→// Note: State capture (tracking untracked files before a session) is handled\\n   313→// by the CLI layer, not the strategy. The strategy receives pre-computed\\n   314→// file lists in StepContext.\\n   315→type Strategy interface {\\n   316→\\t// Name returns the strategy identifier (e.g., \\\"commit\\\", \\\"branch\\\", \\\"stash\\\")\\n   317→\\tName() string\\n   318→\\n   319→\\t// Description returns a human-readable description for the setup wizard\\n   320→\\tDescription() string\\n   321→\\n   322→\\t// ValidateRepository checks if the repository is in a valid state\\n   323→\\t// for this strategy to operate. Returns an error if validation fails.\\n   324→\\tValidateRepository() error\\n   325→\\n   326→\\t// SaveStep is called on Stop to save all session changes\\n   327→\\t// using this strategy's approach (commit, branch, stash, etc.)\\n   328→\\tSaveStep(ctx StepContext) error\\n   329→\\n   330→\\t// SaveTaskStep is called by PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.\\n   331→\\t// Creates a checkpoint commit with task metadata for later rewind.\\n   332→\\t// Different strategies may handle this differently:\\n   333→\\t// - Commit strategy: commits to active branch\\n   334→\\t// - Manual-commit strategy: commits to shadow branch\\n   335→\\t// - Auto-commit strategy: commits logs to shadow only (code deferred to Stop)\\n   336→\\tSaveTaskStep(ctx TaskStepContext) error\\n   337→\\n   338→\\t// GetRewindPoints returns available points to rewind to.\\n   339→\\t// The limit parameter controls the maximum number of points to return.\\n   340→\\tGetRewindPoints(limit int) ([]RewindPoint, error)\\n   341→\\n   342→\\t// Rewind restores the repository to the given rewind point.\\n   343→\\t// The metadataDir in the point is used to restore the session transcript.\\n   344→\\tRewind(point RewindPoint) error\\n   345→\\n   346→\\t// CanRewind checks if rewinding is currently possible.\\n   347→\\t// Returns (canRewind, reason if not, error)\\n   348→\\tCanRewind() (bool, string, error)\\n   349→\\n   350→\\t// PreviewRewind returns what will happen if rewinding to the given point.\\n   351→\\t// This allows showing warnings about files that will be deleted before the rewind.\\n   352→\\t// Returns nil if preview is not supported (e.g., auto-commit strategy).\\n   353→\\tPreviewRewind(point RewindPoint) (*RewindPreview, error)\\n   354→\\n   355→\\t// GetTaskCheckpoint returns the task checkpoint for a given rewind point.\\n   356→\\t// For strategies that store checkpoints in git (auto-commit), this reads from the branch.\\n   357→\\t// For strategies that store checkpoints on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the filesystem.\\n   358→\\t// Returns nil, nil if not a task checkpoint or checkpoint not found.\\n   359→\\tGetTaskCheckpoint(point RewindPoint) (*TaskCheckpoint, error)\\n   360→\\n   361→\\t// GetTaskCheckpointTranscript returns the session transcript for a task checkpoint.\\n   362→\\t// For strategies that store transcripts in git (auto-commit), this reads from the branch.\\n   363→\\t// For strategies that store transcripts on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the filesystem.\\n   364→\\tGetTaskCheckpointTranscript(point RewindPoint) ([]byte, error)\\n   365→\\n   366→\\t// GetSessionInfo returns session information for linking commits.\\n   367→\\t// This is used by the context command to generate trailers.\\n   368→\\t// Returns ErrNoSession if no session info is available.\\n   369→\\tGetSessionInfo() (*SessionInfo, error)\\n   370→\\n   371→\\t// EnsureSetup ensures the strategy's required setup is in place,\\n   372→\\t// installing any missing pieces (git hooks, gitignore entries, etc.).\\n   373→\\t// Returns nil if setup is complete or was successfully installed.\\n   374→\\tEnsureSetup() error\\n   375→\\n   376→\\t// NOTE: ListSessions and GetSession are standalone functions in session.go.\\n   377→\\t// They read from entire/checkpoints/v1 and merge with SessionSource if implemented.\\n   378→\\n   379→\\t// GetMetadataRef returns a reference to the metadata commit for the given checkpoint.\\n   380→\\t// Format: \\\"<branch>@<commit-sha>\\\" (e.g., \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1@abc123\\\").\\n   381→\\t// Returns empty string if not applicable (e.g., commit strategy with filesystem metadata).\\n   382→\\tGetMetadataRef(checkpoint Checkpoint) string\\n   383→\\n   384→\\t// GetSessionMetadataRef returns a reference to the most recent metadata commit for a session.\\n   385→\\t// Format: \\\"<branch>@<commit-sha>\\\" (e.g., \\\"entire/checkpoints/v1@abc123\\\").\\n   386→\\t// Returns empty string if not applicable or session not found.\\n   387→\\tGetSessionMetadataRef(sessionID string) string\\n   388→\\n   389→\\t// GetSessionContext returns the context.md content for a session.\\n   390→\\t// Returns empty string if not available.\\n   391→\\tGetSessionContext(sessionID string) string\\n   392→\\n   393→\\t// GetCheckpointLog returns the session transcript for a specific checkpoint.\\n   394→\\t// For strategies that store transcripts in git branches (auto-commit, manual-commit),\\n   395→\\t// this reads from the checkpoint's commit tree.\\n   396→\\t// For strategies that store on disk (commit), reads from the filesystem.\\n   397→\\t// Returns ErrNoMetadata if transcript is not available.\\n   398→\\tGetCheckpointLog(checkpoint Checkpoint) ([]byte, error)\\n   399→}\\n   400→\\n   401→// SessionInitializer is an optional interface for strategies that need to\\n   402→// initialize session state when a user prompt is submitted.\\n   403→// Strategies like manual-commit use this to create session state files that\\n   404→// the git prepare-commit-msg hook can detect.\\n   405→type SessionInitializer interface {\\n   406→\\t// InitializeSession creates session state for a new session.\\n   407→\\t// Called during UserPromptSubmit hook before any checkpoints are created.\\n   408→\\t// agentType is the human-readable name of the agent (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\").\\n   409→\\t// transcriptPath is the path to the live transcript file (for mid-session commit detection).\\n   410→\\t// userPrompt is the user's prompt text (stored truncated as FirstPrompt for display).\\n   411→\\tInitializeSession(sessionID string, agentType agent.AgentType, transcriptPath string, userPrompt string) error\\n   412→}\\n   413→\\n   414→// PrepareCommitMsgHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to\\n   415→// handle the git prepare-commit-msg hook.\\n   416→type PrepareCommitMsgHandler interface {\\n   417→\\t// PrepareCommitMsg is called by the git prepare-commit-msg hook.\\n   418→\\t// It can modify the commit message file to add trailers, etc.\\n   419→\\t// The source parameter indicates how the commit was initiated:\\n   420→\\t//   - \\\"\\\" or \\\"template\\\": normal editor flow\\n   421→\\t//   - \\\"message\\\": using -m or -F flag\\n   422→\\t//   - \\\"merge\\\": merge commit\\n   423→\\t//   - \\\"squash\\\": squash merge\\n   424→\\t//   - \\\"commit\\\": amend with -c/-C\\n   425→\\t// Should return nil on errors to not block commits (log warnings to stderr).\\n   426→\\tPrepareCommitMsg(commitMsgFile string, source string) error\\n   427→}\\n   428→\\n   429→// PostCommitHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to\\n   430→// handle the git post-commit hook.\\n   431→type PostCommitHandler interface {\\n   432→\\t// PostCommit is called by the git post-commit hook after a commit is created.\\n   433→\\t// Used to perform actions like condensing session data after commits.\\n   434→\\t// Should return nil on errors to not block subsequent operations (log warnings to stderr).\\n   435→\\tPostCommit() error\\n   436→}\\n   437→\\n   438→// CommitMsgHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to\\n   439→// handle the git commit-msg hook.\\n   440→type CommitMsgHandler interface {\\n   441→\\t// CommitMsg is called by the git commit-msg hook after the user edits the message.\\n   442→\\t// Used to validate or modify the final commit message before the commit is created.\\n   443→\\t// If this returns an error, the commit is aborted.\\n   444→\\tCommitMsg(commitMsgFile string) error\\n   445→}\\n   446→\\n   447→// PrePushHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to\\n   448→// handle the git pre-push hook.\\n   449→type PrePushHandler interface {\\n   450→\\t// PrePush is called by the git pre-push hook before pushing to a remote.\\n   451→\\t// Used to push session branches (e.g., entire/checkpoints/v1) alongside user pushes.\\n   452→\\t// The remote parameter is the name of the remote being pushed to.\\n   453→\\t// Should return nil on errors to not block pushes (log warnings to stderr).\\n   454→\\tPrePush(remote string) error\\n   455→}\\n   456→\\n   457→// TurnEndHandler is an optional interface for strategies that need to\\n   458→// perform work when an agent turn ends (ACTIVE → IDLE).\\n   459→// For example, manual-commit strategy uses this to finalize checkpoints\\n   460→// with the full session transcript.\\n   461→type TurnEndHandler interface {\\n   462→\\t// HandleTurnEnd performs strategy-specific cleanup at the end of a turn.\\n   463→\\t// Work items are read from state (e.g. TurnCheckpointIDs), not from the\\n   464→\\t// action list. The state has already been updated by ApplyTransition;\\n   465→\\t// the caller saves it after this method returns.\\n   466→\\tHandleTurnEnd(state *session.State) error\\n   467→}\\n   468→\\n   469→// RestoredSession describes a single session that was restored by RestoreLogsOnly.\\n   470→// Each session may come from a different agent, so callers use this to print\\n   471→// per-session resume commands without re-reading the metadata tree.\\n   472→type RestoredSession struct {\\n   473→\\tSessionID string\\n   474→\\tAgent     agent.AgentType\\n   475→\\tPrompt    string\\n   476→}\\n   477→\\n   478→// LogsOnlyRestorer is an optional interface for strategies that support\\n   479→// restoring session logs without file state restoration.\\n   480→// This is used for \\\"logs-only\\\" rewind points where only the session transcript\\n   481→// can be restored (file state requires git checkout).\\n   482→type LogsOnlyRestorer interface {\\n   483→\\t// RestoreLogsOnly restores session logs from a logs-only rewind point.\\n   484→\\t// Does not modify the working directory - only restores the transcript\\n   485→\\t// to the agent's session directory (determined per-session from checkpoint metadata).\\n   486→\\t// If force is false, prompts for confirmation when local logs have newer timestamps.\\n   487→\\t// Returns info about each restored session so callers can print correct resume commands.\\n   488→\\tRestoreLogsOnly(point RewindPoint, force bool) ([]RestoredSession, error)\\n   489→}\\n   490→\\n   491→// SessionResetter is an optional interface for strategies that support\\n   492→// resetting session state and shadow branches.\\n   493→// This is used by the \\\"reset\\\" command to clean up shadow branches\\n   494→// and session state when a user wants to start fresh.\\n   495→type SessionResetter interface {\\n   496→\\t// Reset deletes the shadow branch and session state for the current HEAD.\\n   497→\\t// Returns nil if there's nothing to reset (no shadow branch).\\n   498→\\tReset() error\\n   499→\\n   500→\\t// ResetSession clears the state for a single session and cleans up\\n   501→\\t// the shadow branch if no other sessions reference it.\\n   502→\\t// File changes remain in the working directory.\\n   503→\\tResetSession(sessionID string) error\\n   504→}\\n   505→\\n   506→// SessionCondenser is an optional interface for strategies that support\\n   507→// force-condensing a session. This is used by \\\"entire doctor\\\" to\\n   508→// salvage stuck sessions by condensing their data to permanent storage.\\n   509→type SessionCondenser interface {\\n   510→\\t// CondenseSessionByID force-condenses a session and cleans up.\\n   511→\\t// Generates a new checkpoint ID, condenses to entire/checkpoints/v1,\\n   512→\\t// updates the session state, and removes the shadow branch\\n   513→\\t// if no other active sessions need it.\\n   514→\\tCondenseSessionByID(sessionID string) error\\n   515→}\\n   516→\\n   517→// ConcurrentSessionChecker is an optional interface for strategies that support\\n   518→// counting concurrent sessions with uncommitted changes.\\n   519→// This is used by the SessionStart hook to show an informational message about\\n   520→// how many other active conversations will be included in the next commit.\\n   521→type ConcurrentSessionChecker interface {\\n   522→\\t// CountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints returns the number of other active sessions\\n   523→\\t// with uncommitted checkpoints on the same base commit.\\n   524→\\t// Returns 0, nil if no such sessions exist.\\n   525→\\tCountOtherActiveSessionsWithCheckpoints(currentSessionID string) (int, error)\\n   526→}\\n   527→\\n   528→// SessionSource is an optional interface for strategies that provide additional\\n   529→// sessions beyond those stored on the entire/checkpoints/v1 branch.\\n   530→// For example, manual-commit strategy provides active sessions from .git/entire-sessions/\\n   531→// that haven't yet been condensed to entire/checkpoints/v1.\\n   532→//\\n   533→// ListSessions() automatically discovers all registered strategies, checks if they\\n   534→// implement SessionSource, and merges their additional sessions by ID.\\n   535→type SessionSource interface {\\n   536→\\t// GetAdditionalSessions returns sessions not yet on entire/checkpoints/v1 branch.\\n   537→\\tGetAdditionalSessions() ([]*Session, error)\\n   538→}\\n   539→\\n   540→// OrphanedItemsLister is an optional interface for strategies that can identify\\n   541→// orphaned items (shadow branches, session states, checkpoints) that should be\\n   542→// cleaned up. This is used by the \\\"entire session cleanup\\\" command.\\n   543→//\\n   544→// ListAllCleanupItems() automatically discovers all registered strategies, checks\\n   545→// if they implement OrphanedItemsLister, and combines their orphaned items.\\n   546→type OrphanedItemsLister interface {\\n   547→\\t// ListOrphanedItems returns items created by this strategy that are now orphaned.\\n   548→\\t// Each strategy defines what \\\"orphaned\\\" means for its own data structures.\\n   549→\\tListOrphanedItems() ([]CleanupItem, error)\\n   550→}\\n   551→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"25ad7b02-dab0-49d3-ae17-bc4f8b3f5d1c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-21T07:28:45.681Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/strategy.go\",\"content\":\"// Package strategy provides an interface for different git strategies\\n// that can be used to save and manage Claude Code session changes.\\npackage strategy\\n\\nimport (\\n\\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n\\n\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id\\\"\\n\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/session\\\"\\n)\\n\\n// ErrNoMetadata is returned when a commit does not have an Entire metadata trailer.\\nvar ErrNoMetadata = errors.New(\\\"commit has no entire metadata\\\")\\n\\n// ErrNoSession is returned when no session info is available.\\nvar ErrNoSession = errors.New(\\\"no session info available\\\")\\n\\n// ErrNotTaskCheckpoint is returned when a rewind point is not a task checkpoint.\\nvar ErrNotTaskCheckpoint = errors.New(\\\"not a task checkpoint\\\")\\n\\n// ErrEmptyRepository is returned when the repository has no commits yet.\\nvar ErrEmptyRepository = errors.New(\\\"repository has no commits yet\\\")\\n\\n// SessionIDConflictError is returned when trying to start a new session\\n// but the shadow branch already has commits from a different session ID.\\n// This prevents orphaning existing session work.\\ntype SessionIDConflictError struct {\\n\\tExistingSession string // Session ID found in the shadow branch\\n\\tNewSession      string // Session ID being initialized\\n\\tShadowBranch    string // The shadow branch name (e.g., \\\"entire/abc1234\\\")\\n}\\n\\nfunc (e *SessionIDConflictError) Error() string {\\n\\treturn \\\"session ID conflict: shadow branch has commits from a different session\\\"\\n}\\n\\n// ExtractToolUseIDFromTaskMetadataDir extracts the ToolUseID from a task metadata directory path.\\n// Task metadata dirs have format: .entire/metadata/<session>/tasks/<toolUseID>\\n// Returns empty string if not a task metadata directory.\\nfunc ExtractToolUseIDFromTaskMetadataDir(metadataDir string) string {\\n\\tparts := strings.Split(metadataDir, \\\"/\\\")\\n\\tif len(parts) >= 2 && parts[len(parts)-2] == \\\"tasks\\\" {\\n\\t\\treturn parts[len(parts)-1]\\n\\t}\\n\\treturn \\\"\\\"\\n}\\n\\n// SessionInfo contains information about the current session state.\\n// This is used to generate trailers for linking commits to their AI session.\\ntype SessionInfo struct {\\n\\t// SessionID is the session identifier extracted from the latest commit's metadata\\n\\tSessionID string\\n\\n\\t// Reference is a strategy-specific reference string.\\n\\t// For manual-commit strategy: \\\"entire/abc1234\\\" (the shadow branch name)\\n\\t// Empty for commit strategy (metadata is in the same commit).\\n\\tReference string\\n\\n\\t// CommitHash is the full SHA of the commit containing the session metadata.\\n\\t// Empty for commit strategy.\\n\\tCommitHash string\\n}\\n\\n// RewindPoint represents a point to which the user can rewind.\\n// This abstraction allows different strategies to use different\\n// identifiers (commit hashes, branch names, stash refs, etc.)\\ntype RewindPoint struct {\\n\\t// ID is the unique identifier for this rewind point\\n\\t// (commit hash, branch name, stash ref, etc.)\\n\\tID string\\n\\n\\t// Message is the human-readable description/summary\\n\\tMessage string\\n\\n\\t// MetadataDir is the path to the metadata directory\\n\\tMetadataDir string\\n\\n\\t// Date is when this rewind point was created\\n\\tDate time.Time\\n\\n\\t// IsTaskCheckpoint indicates if this is a task checkpoint (vs a session checkpoint)\\n\\tIsTaskCheckpoint bool\\n\\n\\t// ToolUseID is the tool use ID for task checkpoints (empty for session checkpoints)\\n\\tToolUseID string\\n\\n\\t// IsLogsOnly indicates this is a commit with session logs but no shadow branch state.\\n\\t// The logs can be restored from entire/checkpoints/v1, but file state requires git checkout.\\n\\tIsLogsOnly bool\\n\\n\\t// CheckpointID is the stable 12-hex-char identifier for logs-only points.\\n\\t// Used to retrieve logs from entire/checkpoints/v1/<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/full.jsonl\\n\\t// Empty for shadow branch checkpoints (uncommitted).\\n\\tCheckpointID id.CheckpointID\\n\\n\\t// Agent is the human-readable name of the agent that created this checkpoint\\n\\t// (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\")\\n\\tAgent agent.AgentType\\n\\n\\t// SessionID is the session identifier for this checkpoint.\\n\\t// Used to distinguish checkpoints from different concurrent sessions.\\n\\tSessionID string\\n\\n\\t// SessionPrompt is the initial prompt that started this session.\\n\\t// Used to help users identify which session a checkpoint belongs to.\\n\\tSessionPrompt string\\n\\n\\t// SessionCount is the number of sessions in this checkpoint (1 for single-session).\\n\\t// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.\\n\\tSessionCount int\\n\\n\\t// SessionIDs contains all session IDs when this is a multi-session checkpoint.\\n\\t// The last entry is the most recent session (same as SessionID).\\n\\t// Only populated for logs-only points with multi-session checkpoints.\\n\\tSessionIDs []string\\n\\n\\t// SessionPrompts contains the first prompt for each session (parallel to SessionIDs).\\n\\t// Used to display context when showing resume commands for multi-session checkpoints.\\n\\tSessionPrompts []string\\n}\\n\\n// RewindPreview describes what will happen when rewinding to a checkpoint.\\n// Used to warn users about files that will be modified or deleted.\\ntype RewindPreview struct {\\n\\t// FilesToRestore are files from the checkpoint that will be written/restored.\\n\\tFilesToRestore []string\\n\\n\\t// FilesToDelete are untracked files that will be removed.\\n\\t// These are files created after the checkpoint that aren't in the checkpoint tree\\n\\t// and weren't present at session start.\\n\\tFilesToDelete []string\\n\\n\\t// TrackedChanges are tracked files with uncommitted changes that will be reverted.\\n\\t// These come from the existing CanRewind() warning.\\n\\tTrackedChanges []string\\n}\\n\\n// StepContext contains all information needed for saving a step checkpoint.\\n// All file paths should be pre-filtered and normalized by the CLI layer.\\ntype StepContext struct {\\n\\t// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier\\n\\tSessionID string\\n\\n\\t// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified during the session\\n\\t// (extracted from the transcript, already filtered and relative)\\n\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n\\n\\t// NewFiles is the list of new files created during the session\\n\\t// (pre-computed by CLI from pre-prompt state comparison)\\n\\tNewFiles []string\\n\\n\\t// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted during the session\\n\\t// (tracked files that no longer exist)\\n\\tDeletedFiles []string\\n\\n\\t// MetadataDir is the path to the session metadata directory\\n\\tMetadataDir string\\n\\n\\t// MetadataDirAbs is the absolute path to the session metadata directory\\n\\tMetadataDirAbs string\\n\\n\\t// CommitMessage is the generated commit message\\n\\tCommitMessage string\\n\\n\\t// TranscriptPath is the path to the transcript file\\n\\tTranscriptPath string\\n\\n\\t// AuthorName is the name to use for commits\\n\\tAuthorName string\\n\\n\\t// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits\\n\\tAuthorEmail string\\n\\n\\t// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\")\\n\\tAgentType agent.AgentType\\n\\n\\t// Transcript position at step/turn start - tracks what was added during this step\\n\\tStepTranscriptIdentifier string // Last identifier when step started (UUID for Claude, message ID for Gemini)\\n\\tStepTranscriptStart      int    // Transcript line count when this step/turn started\\n\\n\\t// TokenUsage contains the token usage for this checkpoint\\n\\tTokenUsage *agent.TokenUsage\\n}\\n\\n// TaskStepContext contains all information needed for saving a task step checkpoint.\\n// This is called by the PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.\\n// The strategy is responsible for creating metadata structures and storing them\\n// according to its storage approach.\\ntype TaskStepContext struct {\\n\\t// SessionID is the Claude Code session identifier\\n\\tSessionID string\\n\\n\\t// ToolUseID is the unique identifier for this Task tool invocation\\n\\tToolUseID string\\n\\n\\t// AgentID is the subagent identifier (from tool_response.agentId)\\n\\tAgentID string\\n\\n\\t// ModifiedFiles is the list of files modified by the subagent\\n\\t// (extracted from the subagent's transcript)\\n\\tModifiedFiles []string\\n\\n\\t// NewFiles is the list of new files created by the subagent\\n\\t// (computed from pre-task state comparison)\\n\\tNewFiles []string\\n\\n\\t// DeletedFiles is the list of files deleted by the subagent\\n\\tDeletedFiles []string\\n\\n\\t// TranscriptPath is the path to the main session transcript\\n\\tTranscriptPath string\\n\\n\\t// SubagentTranscriptPath is the path to the subagent's transcript (if available)\\n\\tSubagentTranscriptPath string\\n\\n\\t// CheckpointUUID is the UUID for transcript truncation when rewinding\\n\\tCheckpointUUID string\\n\\n\\t// AuthorName is the name to use for commits\\n\\tAuthorName string\\n\\n\\t// AuthorEmail is the email to use for commits\\n\\tAuthorEmail string\\n\\n\\t// IsIncremental indicates this is an incremental checkpoint during task execution,\\n\\t// not a final task completion checkpoint. When true:\\n\\t// - Writes to checkpoints/NNN-{tool-use-id}.json instead of checkpoint.json\\n\\t// - Skips transcript handling\\n\\t// - Uses incremental commit message\\n\\tIsIncremental bool\\n\\n\\t// IncrementalSequence is the checkpoint sequence number (1, 2, 3, ...)\\n\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n\\tIncrementalSequence int\\n\\n\\t// IncrementalType is the tool that triggered this checkpoint (\\\"TodoWrite\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", etc.)\\n\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n\\tIncrementalType string\\n\\n\\t// IncrementalData is the tool_input payload for this checkpoint\\n\\t// Only used when IsIncremental is true\\n\\tIncrementalData json.RawMessage\\n\\n\\t// SubagentType is the type of subagent (e.g., \\\"dev\\\", \\\"reviewer\\\")\\n\\t// Extracted from tool_input.subagent_type in Task tool\\n\\t// Used for descriptive commit messages\\n\\tSubagentType string\\n\\n\\t// TaskDescription is the task description provided to the subagent\\n\\t// Extracted from tool_input.description in Task tool\\n\\t// Used for descriptive commit messages\\n\\tTaskDescription string\\n\\n\\t// TodoContent is the content of the in-progress todo item\\n\\t// Extracted from tool_input.todos where status == \\\"in_progress\\\"\\n\\t// Used for descriptive incremental checkpoint messages\\n\\tTodoContent string\\n\\n\\t// AgentType is the human-readable agent name (e.g., \\\"Claude Code\\\", \\\"Cursor\\\")\\n\\tAgentType agent.AgentType\\n}\\n\\n// TaskCheckpoint contains the checkpoint information written to checkpoint.json\\ntype TaskCheckpoint struct {\\n\\tSessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n\\tToolUseID      string `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"`\\n\\tCheckpointUUID string `json:\\\"checkpoint_uuid\\\"`\\n\\tAgentID        string `json:\\\"agent_id,omitempty\\\"`\\n}\\n\\n// SubagentCheckpoint represents an intermediate checkpoint created during subagent execution.\\n// These are created by PostToolUse hooks for tools like TodoWrite, Edit, Write.\\ntype SubagentCheckpoint struct {\\n\\tType      string          `json:\\\"type\\\"`        // Tool name: \\\"TodoWrite\\\", \\\"Edit\\\", \\\"Write\\\"\\n\\tToolUseID string          `json:\\\"tool_use_id\\\"` // The tool use ID that created this checkpoint\\n\\tTimestamp time.Time       `json:\\\"timestamp\\\"`   // When the checkpoint was created\\n\\tData      json.RawMessage `json:\\\"data\\\"`        // Type-specific payload (tool_input)\\n}\\n\\n// TaskMetadataDir returns the path to a task's metadata directory\\n// within the session metadata directory.\\nfunc TaskMetadataDir(sessionMetadataDir, toolUseID string) string {\\n\\treturn sessionMetadataDir + \\\"/tasks/\\\" + toolUseID\\n}\\n\\n// ReadTaskCheckpoint reads the checkpoint.json file from a task metadata directory.\\n// This is used during rewind to get the checkpoint UUID for transcript truncation.\\nfunc ReadTaskCheckpoint(taskMetadataDir string) (*TaskCheckpoint, error) {\\n\\tcheckpointFile := taskMetadataDir + \\\"/checkpoint.json\\\"\\n\\n\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(checkpointFile) //nolint:gosec // Reading from controlled git metadata path\\n\\tif err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn nil, err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\tvar checkpoint TaskCheckpoint\\n\\tif err := json.Unmarshal(data, &checkpoint); err != nil {\\n\\t\\treturn nil, err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase\\n\\t}\\n\\n\\treturn &checkpoint, nil\\n}\\n\\n// Strategy defines the interface for git operation strategies.\\n// Different implementations can use commits, branches, stashes, etc.\\n//\\n// Note: State capture (tracking untracked files before a session) is handled\\n// by the CLI layer, not the strategy. The strategy receives pre-computed\\n// file lists in StepContext.\\ntype Strategy interface {\\n\\t// Name returns the strategy identifier (e.g., \\\"commit\\\", \\\"branch\\\", \\\"stash\\\")\\n\\tName() string\\n\\n\\t// Description returns a human-readable description for the setup wizard\\n\\tDescription() string\\n\\n\\t// ValidateRepository checks if the repository is in a valid state\\n\\t// for this strategy to operate. Returns an error if validation fails.\\n\\tValidateRepository() error\\n\\n\\t// SaveStep is called on Stop to save all session changes\\n\\t// using this strategy's approach (commit, branch, stash, etc.)\\n\\tSaveStep(ctx StepContext) error\\n\\n\\t// SaveTaskStep is called by PostToolUse[Task] hook when a subagent completes.\\n\\t// Creates a checkpoint commit with task metadata for later rewind.\\n\\t// Different strategies may handle this differently:\\n\\t// - Commit strategy: commits to active branch\\n\\t// - Manual-commit strategy: commits to shadow branch\\n\\t// - Auto-commit strategy: commits logs to shadow only (code deferred to Stop)\\n\\tSaveTaskStep(ctx TaskStepContext) error\\n\\n\\t// GetRewindPoints returns available points to rewind to.\\n\\t// The limit parameter controls the maximum number of points to return.\\n\\tGetRewindPoints(limit int) ([]RewindPoint, error)\\n\\n\\t// Rewind restores the repository to the given rewind point.\\n\\t// The metadataDir in the point is used to restore the session transcript.\\n\\tRewind(point RewindPoint) error\\n\\n\\t// CanRewind checks if rewinding is currently possible.\\n\\t// Returns (canRewind, reason if not, error)\\n\\tCanRewind() (bool, string, error)\\n\\n\\t// PreviewRewind returns what will happen if rewinding to the given point.\\n\\t// This allows showing warnings about files that will be deleted before the rewind.\\n\\t// Returns nil if preview is not supported (e.g., auto-commit strategy).\\n\\tPreviewRewind(point RewindPoint) (*RewindPreview, error)\\n\\n\\t// GetTaskCheckpoint returns the task checkpoint for a given rewind point.\\n\\t// For strategies that store checkpoints in git (auto-commit), this reads from the branch.\\n\\t// For strategies that store checkpoints on disk (commit, manual-commit), this reads from the file